name: Kliv
businessDescription:
Kliv is an agentic AI platform that builds web applications through interactive conversation. 

Unlike the first generation of AI builders that generate everything in a single reply, Kliv works like a real developer - thinking through requirements, inspecting files, creating a todo-list, making iterative changes, and refining code step-by-step.
longBusinessDescription:
Kliv is an agentic AI platform that builds web applications through interactive conversation. 
Unlike the first generation of AI builders that generate everything in a single reply, Kliv works like a real developer - thinking through requirements, creating a todo-list, inspecting files, making iterative changes, and refining code step-by-step.
Watch as the AI reasons through your project, asks clarifying questions, and methodically builds your application.
Perfect for rapid prototyping, entrepreneurs, and businesses who want professional applications without the technical complexity.
Start with a library of pre-built apps and websites or build from scratch - either way, you'll have a custom website for yourself, your business, or an internal tool in minutes. 
Your application gets free hosting on kliv.site from day one, with instant deployment and no configuration needed. When you're ready to go live, upgrade to a custom domain while keeping all your development tools in one place.
The built-in workspace lets you edit code directly, preview changes before publishing, and maintain complete revision history so you can roll back to any previous version.
Stage updates to test them thoroughly before your users see them.
Connect to GitHub for source control when your team grows, or export your entire codebase anytime. 
Every tool you need for professional app development is integrated into a single platform, from initial prototype through production deployment and ongoing updates. Invite your entire team with unlimited users and role-based access control.
Currently powered by Supabase for reliable backend infrastructure, Kliv is evolving to include a fully integrated backend that will give every app database, authentication, and API capabilities out of the box.

name: Chik
businessDescription: Chik is the most easy-to-use task manager for freelancers and small teams.
longBusinessDescription:
Chik – The collaborative task manager for freelancers
Chik is the answer to bloated, overly complicated, and sluggish project management software (looking at you Notion and Monday). It's the only task manager built specifically for freelancers and offers only what you actually need:
Time tracking: Track within Chik, per-task. Clients can see the total time tracked. Only you can see the individual log history.
Client dashboard: Give your clients a dedicated dashboard to submit, view, and edit tasks as well as communicate with the built in context-aware chat.
Team members: Even freelancers occasionally bring someone onboard, so invite them directly to your Chik team.
Live chat: Use our context-aware live chat to keep client communication focused. Bye bye Slack, Email, WhatsApp.
How is Chik different?
Chik was born from genuine freelancer frustration.
After years of running my own web studio, I (Jonathan, the founder) found myself constantly battling with task management tools that seemed designed for everyone except me.
Notion demanded endless customization before I could even begin working. Asana and Monday buried essential functions under complex workflows meant for large teams.
Every morning, I'd waste precious billable time clicking through bloated interfaces just to figure out what needed my attention.
That's why I created Chik—a task manager that respects a freelancer's time and workflow. Unlike the corporate-focused alternatives, Chik strips away unnecessary features and focuses exclusively on what independent professionals actually need: clear task visibility, straightforward client collaboration, and contextual communication—all in one uncluttered interface.
Chik isn't trying to be everything for everyone; it's specifically crafted for freelancers who need simplicity and efficiency, by someone who lived their challenges firsthand.
Pricing That Makes Sense
Chik is free for freelancers working with their first couple of clients or small team. As your business grows, our affordable pricing scales with you: just €11/month for unlimited client connections and team members. No complex tiers or hidden fees, just straightforward value for independent professionals.
tags: Freelancer Task Manager, Time Tracking, Client Dashboard, Project Collaboration, Live Chat, Team Management, Simple Workflow, Chik App, Notion Alternative, Freelance Productivity

name: Jord AB
businessDescription: Jord is a Swedish company founded in 2017 and headquartered in Stockholm, dedicated to rebalancing the carbon cycle through the production of solid biofuels from C4 grass.
longBusinessDescription:
Jord is a Swedish company founded in 2017 and based in Stockholm, committed to rebalancing the carbon cycle through the production of the next generation of solid biofuels.
At Jord, we envision a future free of fossil fuel emissions. Our approach harnesses nature’s potential to produce renewable fuels without using farmland for food production or wood from forests.
Our holistic approach uses C4 grass, grown on marginal and degraded land in the tropics, as the primary feedstock for renewable, CO₂e-negative solid biofuels. Jord addresses three key challenges:
• Revitalizing degraded land,
• Reducing dependency on fossil fuels, and
• Lowering atmospheric CO₂ levels.
Our regenerative agroforestry model uses C4 grasses to absorb CO₂ and store it in their tissues, root systems, and soil, enriching and improving soil health over time. With the harvested grass, we produce two primary products:
• Solid biofuels, a sustainable energy source for heat and power generation in industry.
• Biochar, which is added to soil to enhance fertility, improve crop yields, and increase soil quality. Biochar remains stable for centuries, locking carbon in the soil long-term.
Additionally, Jord offers tailored carbon credits for businesses seeking to offset their carbon emissions by compensating for unavoidable emissions within their value chains.
tags: Biofuels, Carbon Credits, Biochar, Regenerative agriculture

PaperShell has the core belief that solutions to the climate crisis and a sustainable management of resources is found in nature. We reverse engineer paper back into high tech 3D-wood components: Stronger than plastics, versatile like glass fibre and lighter than aluminium. Enabling companies to switch materials in new or existing products. Helping them substantially decrease CO2 impact as well as enabling them to transition towards a circular bio economy. We’re taking a pioneering role in the transformation towards a local and circular biobased society. Hindering large amounts of GHG emissions entering the atmosphere aiming for carbon net zero (COP21), regeneration (COP15) and beyond.
PaperShell AB was founded in 2021. The first component tests were carried in 2018 but the original idea behind PaperShell was based on the urgent needs for middle management to find and secure feasible, stable and large enough volumes of sustainable and preferably bio-based material solutions.
We’re a diverse and purpose-driven team cross breeding design, science and industrial technology. Inspired by nature’s 3.8 billion years of bio intelligence. In our highly automated production lines we produce our clients print-to-build B2B components that replace bulk materials like wood veneer, plastics, fibre composites and metals such as press moulded aluminium parts.
PaperShell is collaborating with some of the world's best-known brands to switch their components in their products to PaperShell’s material solutions. From our highly automated green factories in Tibro, and with our showroom in Stockholm, we support partners all over the globe in their transition from fossil-based or environmentally hazardous material solutions to 100% biogenic composites.

longBusinessDescription: Charly is a fintech company working to prevent the economic inequalities that occur when starting a family. Charly was founded in 2022 with a mission to bring financial freedom to women. We want to reduce the gap between men and women's lifetime income, starting with creating opportunities for equal pensions. Charly has a unique platform that helps parents understand the economic effect of how they have divided family responsibilities. Responsibilities such as parental leave, part-time work to take care of the family, and staying home with sick children. After calculating and visualizing the economic effect these choices have on your lifetime income, Charly offers a "Love Insurance" to compensate for the inequalities. The insurance is a long-term savings plan in which you together as a couple set aside savings to make up for the unequal division. The insurance also ensures financial compensation in case of separation or divorce. Since almost 50% of marriages in Sweden end in divorce, the compensation for unpaid work to take care of the family is a critical gender equality issue.From now on all families can take action to become more financially equal with Charly.

name: Flatpack
businessDescription:
Flatpack is a deep tech and green AI startup. 

Our vision is to leverage the capabilities of edge computing, providing affordable and streamlined hyperautomation solutions for businesses, consumers, and governments alike. Whether you are pre-training from scratch or fine-tuning language models, Flatpack will seamlessly convert human and sensor input into practical solutions for real-world challenges. 

In essence, we are building "the Arduino of AI" where Flatpack is a development platform (and philosophy) that is tailored for working with micro (100M to 10B parameters) and nano (less than 100M parameters) language models. At its core, Flatpack is an open-source (Apache 2.0) Python package (https://pypi.org/project/flatpack/) that allows developers to develop and/or package their AI and ML-powered projects as flatpacks (FPKs), optimized for easy and widespread deployment on edge computing devices. Among other features, it comes with its own orchestration templates written in TOML and a built-in vector database. On top of that, we are developing fpk.ai, which will be the commercial flowchart-based and low-code editor that will allow everyone from academics to farmers or students to apply artificial intelligence and machine learning to everyday real-world problems (everything from agriculture to space exploration), be it for prototyping or production.

Through the "appification" of AI and ML, in our FPKs, we strive to engage the open source community in creating all kinds of "ready-to-assemble building blocks" that people can use to make their own "things" in an endless cycle of open AI innovation (just like Arduino did with physical computing). Because where is the floppy disk or game cartridge of the AI age?

longBusinessDescription:
MODSIM Pharma specializes in computational chemistry solutions for accelerating drug discovery processes. Our proprietary software suite, developed from renowned academic research at Uppsala University, offers physics-based tools for virtual compound library design, accurate pharmacological target modeling, and candidate compound optimization.
We address the challenges of costly and time-consuming drug discovery by providing efficient computational protocols that expedite hit identification, hit to lead and lead optimization. Our suite of tools is designed to streamline workflows, enhance automation, and improve the accuracy of predictions, ultimately reducing the time and resources required for drug development. We have special expertise in G Protein-Coupled Receptor (GPCR) modeling. 
MODSIM operates through software licensing, consulting services, and ongoing scientific development. We collaborate closely with clients to tailor solutions to their specific needs and objectives. Our commitment to scientific excellence drives us to continually refine and optimize our methodologies, ensuring that we remain at the forefront of computational chemistry innovation.

The current legacy system for importing and exporting coffee has remained unchanged and has led to huge fluctuations in prices that are not always beneficial to the farmer or end consumer. The model (old and proposed new) can be seen at https://farmerscorner.co/Home/FAQ
This old model is burdened with middlemen who do not provide added value to the coffee supply chain. The new model allows farmers themselves to set prices that in turn benefit the end consumer as the price is based on farmers' input costs as well as logistical costs that are easy to manage. This means inflation will not be 'artificial' and the farmers enjoy the ability to have more power in deciding the price of sourced coffee.

name: Digmak
businessDescription: Digmak is a one stop shop for all things related to taxes in the gig-economy. Our all in one platform offers basic tools, increased access to cross-border tax information and a wide network of international tax experts, the new generation of professionals. Digmak is a platform where users can find & book international tax experts. The database of tax regulations & typical cases helps simulate answers, saving time & money for users. Our platform does not provide consulting services but rather a database of international tax firms and smart matchmaking for freelancers, digital nomads, expats and MSMEs. Digmak envisions bringing mobility in tax consulting and digitalizing the traditional taxation process.
longBusinessDescription:
Digmak caters to the new generation of professionals who travel more, are expats, freelancers & digital nomads. It is becoming the norm & with the pandemic, an accelerated trend. Most of big companies have recently jumped on the bandwagon of “Work from Anywhere”. 
The lifestyle is attractive but living & moving to different countries creates huge tax hassles. Furthermore, obtaining access to tax regulations in english, inter-governmental policies & tax experts with international expertise is a rising problem. Relying on traditional methods such as expensive accounting firms & law firms with little international experience is no longer a viable option. Local experts do not like to cater to this international community, who requires more attention & support. 
Hence, we conducted surveys, collected feedback from the nomad community & case scenarios from experts to understand the extent of the problem. We even handled various international client requests ourselves. 
To solve this problem better, Digmak is rolling out our platform, to connect nomads & experts, in September. The project lays the basic foundation of mobility in tax consulting much like the stripped down, platform version of KRY.  The platform answers the need for a global directory of international tax experts available remotely & the future demand for a smarter solution to save time.
Our partnerships with 13 tax consulting firms serving 14 popular nomad destination countries in Europe gives us a huge boost. Lack of nomad solutions in the post pandemic era creates a golden opportunity for us. With few competitors focusing on this target audience, we are early to market with many eager to partner with us.
With a validated MVP and product market fit launching, we’ll start collecting data & search patterns that will enable our smart platform & later our app, making tax consulting more mobile & flexible.
Digmak will soon operate on a hybrid model of pay as you go & SaaS. Bringing the ease of KRY to tax consulting will be a game-changer due to its simplicity & global demand.

name: Peyya
businessDescription: Peyya is a DeFi fintech, developing the next-generation of payment infrastructure and services. At Peyya we are fueled by the fundamental belief that increased trust and financial freedom, create opportunities and financial inclusion that liberates people to live life to its fullest. By bridging the gap between traditional banking and decentralized finance, we bring the next generation of DeFi infrastructure based on blockchain rails and distributed ledger technology, to the masses. Our SaaS platform brings together everything needed in order to issue bank-regulated electronic money in currencies such as EUR, SEK, GBP, along with the infrastructure and building blocks to design and implement blockchain-powered payments in any solution. Transactions are made on blockchain rails over a global payments network and therefore directly between sender-receiver without any routing or intermediaries. With a state of the art atomic swap technology, the transaction, clearing and settlement are done in one single request and performed instantaneously. Not only does this reduce cost and mitigates risk to virtually zero. It also means that money can now flow continuously, effortlessly and safe between people, companies, and nations all over the world in any way they choose. Without the boundaries of intermediaries and legacy technology. All while gaining improved transparency, traceability, and accountability. And this, we believe, will empower people and entrepreneurs to join and thrive in in both the creator economy and global economy. And it will contribute to democratising society, reducing poverty, and creating a sustainable financial ecosystem.

name: NxNANO AB
businessDescription:
In short, our solution is about utilizing liquid flows in all heating and cooling systems and with a simple injection of HTF Compact during ongoing operation increase heat or cooling capacity which radically reduces electricity consumption and other loads on existing systems and is experienced positively by users.
When it comes to radiators, users experience a better and more even heat from the radiator. For property owners, a simple, fast energy efficiency with fast payoff and large measurable CO2 reduction.
longBusinessDescription:
NxNANO AB
We are a company that wants to contribute to building a more sustainable future by thinking a little outside the box. With our curiosity, experience, energy and drive, we are not afraid to take the calculated risks that introductions of new products and services on the market entail.
Many companies focus heavily on finding innovative ways to reduce energy consumption around the world and create added value that enables companies and real estate to maintain their profitability, as global energy reserves are depleted and energy costs continue to rise.
The conventional heat transfer systems associated with industries such as microelectronics, transportation, manufacturing, power generation, heat transfer in real estate and many other technologies have lagged behind. Cooling is a major challenge for many industries, where the operation of equipment can produce a large amount of excess heat, and this may soon hamper the development of future technologies in terms of design and efficiency.
Liquids are often used in refrigeration systems to dissipate heat or maintain an even temperature, but a "nanofliquid" refrigerant can significantly improve the cooling process, which benefits a number of industries, such as industrial machinery, electric motors, medical equipment, power generation and the process industry.
This also applies to the reverse in heating systems where "nano liquids" conduct heat much faster and thereby reduce the load on pumps and other equipment. Water is the most common liquid in all heating systems in properties. HTF Compact together with our product WES - water-improving solution to stabilize that the right PH value is in the system is tomorrow's coolant.
In short, our solution is about utilizing liquid flows in all heating and cooling systems and with a simple injection of HTF Compact during ongoing operation increase heat or cooling capacity which radically reduces electricity consumption and other loads on existing systems and is experienced positively by users.
When it comes to radiators, users experience a better and more even heat from the radiator. For property owners, a simple, fast energy efficiency with fast payoff and large measurable CO2 reduction.
OUR BUSINESS IDEA
Our business idea is to, together with selected strategic partners, introduce and together offer new both cost- and energy- and environmentally efficient complete solutions in areas such as Real Estate, Schools, Hotels, Arenas, Datacenters, the Food Industry and other Industries that have heating / cooling-intensive operations
Against this background, we have established collaborations with some of the leading players in heating, cooling and property automation in the Baltic Sea area.
It is now our intention to, in close collaboration with these, introduce HTF Compact®,. a patented nanobasic solution that can be injected during ongoing operation into most closed, liquid-based heating and cooling systems and that can improve energy consumption by up to 40%.
The patents are held by Italian TCT Nanotech, a business area within TCT SRL.
NxNano AB has the exclusive market rights to HTF Compact® in the Nordic and Baltic countries.

name: Layke Analytics
businessDescription: Layke is an API solution for intelligent screening and matching of candidates. Trained on a large amount of data, our algorithm has the capacity to read, interpret and analyze resumes as a human resource, but faster. What has always been largely done by a human being can now be done by a machine.
longBusinessDescription:
Layke gains access to its customers through a single integration. By integrating Layke with third-party suppliers, we have the opportunity to reach a broad customer base via a single integration. In this way, the product is scalable. 
In an ever-growing market, Layke supports recruiting companies to fill in positions faster and more efficiently based on clear and objective data. Our algorithm transforms a process where the unconscious human bias sometimes can’t be avoided and encourages transparent, skill-based recruitment. 
Trained on a large amount of data, Layke’s algorithm has the capacity to structure, read and analyse documents as a human resource, but faster. The solution is built using advanced machine learning technology and can be seamlessly integrated with existing systems through a single API. 
Supported by advanced machine learning technology, Layke can be divided into two parts: extracting information from documents and matching them with each other. When extracting the unstructured information, Layke uses modern machine learning technology where graph networks are in focus. When it comes to matching, with the help of language comprehension (NLP), Layke can compare different candidates to a job advertisement and answer which ones match best. By learning to group words together, the language model learns to understand different word classes but also which words belong together.
Among many competitive factors, the true strength of the solution lies in that it works on material that all candidates already have, and in systems already used by Layke’s customers.  
Layke's technical solution is based on a combination of language models and graph networks, which makes our algorithm unique, thus not possible to copy.
Moreover, we have built our own tool for data labelling, meaning that we can identify raw data so that a machine learning model can learn from it and make predictions on new data.
And last but not least, our team possesses domain knowledge as well as technical expertise, which enables us to look at the solution from two crucial perspectives.

name: NanoScientifica Scandinavia
businessDescription: NanoScientifica Scandinavia AB is producing high-quality metallic nanoparticles with tight size-and-shape control in a scalable and sustainable way. NanoScientifica Scandinavia is dedicated to sustainability and will whenever possible strive to produce our products with a minimal environmental footprint. This means that we strive towards using recycled metal sources and develop synthesis routes with minimal waste under closed-loop processes.
longBusinessDescription:
Efficient and safe materials for Energy production and energy storage are critical for a sustainable society. In this context, nanomaterials with controlled size and shape offer great opportunities for a broad range of applications, including fuel cells, sensors, electronic devices, displays, and medical technology.
Many of these nanomaterials have been discovered in research laboratories during recent decades, but are not available in larger quantities due to challenges with productions and scale-up.
Based on almost 20 years of experience in nanomaterials synthesis, professor Kasper Moth-Poulsen, and post-doc researchers Jessica Orrego Hernandez and Robson Rosa da Silva have now formed the company NanoScientifica Scandinavia AB that seeks to make nanoparticles with unprecedented control over size and shape available for companies and research groups that are tackling some of the greatest challenges of our time. What we have discovered is a way to continuously produce these materials at very high quality with almost no waste.
The team's first 3 products that available today are i) palladium nanocubes that have used in fuel cells, sensing, and catalysis. Ii) Gold nanospheres that can be used in biomedical, photonics, and sensing applications and iii) Silver Nanowires with possible use in displays and advanced solar cells. Several more products will be added in the coming months.
tags: circular economy, recycled,  shape-and-size controlled nanoparticles, energy

More resource-efficient. Raw data is processed in the platform, which means that the customer does not need to do any manual pre-processing of the data. This can save up to 90% of the time data owners spend on sustainability data reporting.
Providing higher quality results, as human input is minimized and thereby also the risk for manual errors. Further, quality checks are continuously applied throughout the platform to increase data quality. In comparison, using competitors’ platforms, the quality of the data that is inputted to the platform is the quality that is outputted, and risk for manual errors are significant as raw data is not processed.
The ease of using the platform and the reduction in time spent on processing data sources leads to the ultimate goal of the SustainLab platform: to accelerate the sustainability transition of businesses worldwide, as companies are enabled to view their performance and data once per month or even once per week, instead of once yearly.
Presenting additional unique information to the customer, such as extensive benchmarking to standards and peers, and target tracking.
As a result, SustainLab enables decision makers to achieve impactful results in their business. With this, we aim to fulfill our vision: To accelerate change for better business - better planet.

There is a great need to develop faster and more cost-efficient screening tools. Early detection would benefit researchers in the quest to find reliable treatments, and subsequently that would benefit patients, caregivers, and society in whole.
ADix is a smartphone-based app that utilizes machine learning technology to identify digital phenotypes for early detection of dementia.

name: New Logic
businessDescription: We believe that sustainability-demands must drive future disruptive innovations because we need behavioral change to solve the climate crisis. Digital marketing is a force for transformation and accelerated progress. Consequently, we aim to drive social and behavioral change by boosting businesses and brands actively improving current systems’ efficiency and driving positive exponential change. We strive to create substantial value, focus on results, and stay flexible in our approach. Selective measures do not sit well with us. We believe in long-term goals and lasting results. We do not latch on to a single discipline but instead aim to build a complete strategy, including considering each phase our clients go through during their yearly cycle (i.e., omni-channel mindset). Grönbil.se tar upp kampen mot jättarna med endast miljöbilar
I februari 2019 rullades Grönbil.se ut och på bara några månader hade sajten dragit till sig över 100 bilhandlare och mer än 500 miljöbilar.
longBusinessDescription:
”Det ligger rätt i tiden. Vi ser en stor omställning i bilbranschen och inte minst den stora satsningen på elbilar. Dessutom förändras kundernas beteende hela tiden och alltfler vill kunna köpa bilen på nätet.” säger Ned, en av grundarna.
 Grönbil.se är en miljöbilsajt där du kan köpa och sälja miljöbilar, läsa varierande nyheter från bilvärlden, hitta handlare och verkstäder nära dig, kartsöka landets laddningsstationer och mycket mer. Bakom Grönbil.se står Peter, initiativtagaren med lång erfarenhet av bilbranschen bl. a. tidigare ägare av Kareby bil i Kungälv och hans kollega Ned, webbentreprenören med tidigare kopplingar till KVD och Bilweb.
”Det är solklart att bilbranschen och bilhandeln behöver tänka nytt. Alla som har något med bilhandeln att göra är överens om att kunderna i dag är mer pålästa än någonsin. Förr blev det fyra-fem besök hos bilhandlaren innan det blev affär. Idag sker det oftast vid första besöket. Kunden vet exakt vad den vill ha när den kommer in och i praktiken har den redan bestämt sig.” säger Peter.
Vi går mot en tid där återförsäljarnas roll minimeras och alltfler affärer sker direkt på nätet.
Exempelvis har Tesla helt valt bort återförsäljarledet och vi ser andra biltillverkare hoppa på samma trend. Sedan har vi tydliga klimatmål 2030 där majoriteten av bilarna ska vara rena miljöbilar. Sverige ligger väldigt bra till i denna omställning och efterfrågan för miljöbilar ökar konstant för varje år. Grönbil.se ser sig som en seriös konkurrent till de stora jättarna och tror sig kunna ta marknadsandelar genom att sätta kunden och miljön i fokus och göra det på ett innovativt sätt.

This time, the impact on our businesses and lives will be even greater. With the promise of exponential growth, the 4th industrial revolution is set to disrupt every industry in every country. Oak Universe is the catalyst that will change not only the investment landscape, but how companies and societies operate. The future belongs to those who are able to manage uncertainty and innovate rapidly. Oak Universe provides companies with the funding and expertise to unleash the power and possibilities of the fourth industrial revolution.
tags: Business Development, Electronics, Financial Services, Information Technology, Medical

name: OMEN Technologies AB
businessDescription: Omen was acquired by Clavister during October 2021. Omen is an AI driven cybersecurity solution with a patented methodology. Our purpose is to contribute to a secure connected society! We help the IIoT industry to stay connected, protected & optimized by our AI driven security-analysis platform. Our automated platform monitors and detects cyber threats, faults and anomalies. We provide intelligence so our clients can make better decisions. Our security solution has extremely high precision, its highly compressible and its acting locally which makes it extremely efficient and sustainable as it does not need to encrypt tons of security data. So much energy waste will be avoided, and our connected vehicles and society in general will be much safer.

name: FLOAT
businessDescription: Traditional finance hasn't kept up with innovation. The funding process for SME SaaS companies is antiquated, hard to access, time-consuming, and tedious. That's  why at Float we pioneered a new product, we like to call Capital-as-a-service (CaaS). We provide SaaS startups and SMEs with fast, easy, founder-friendly, and non-dilutive growth capital. As founders ourselves, our vision is to empower other founders by providing them the capital they need to focus on building and growing their business without entering a never-ending fundraising mode.
tags: Financial Services, Lending, Security, Venture Capital

name: Oterlu
businessDescription: Oterlu AI develops state of the art Artificial Intelligence algorithms to automatically detect and take action when for example someone is harassing another person in a social interaction. The technology employs Natural Language Processing to fully understand the intent of someone. This allows platforms be it a game, forum or chat to build a healthy and thriving community that continues to grow.

name: Fixi
businessDescription: We are digitizing the biking ecosystem by connecting all stakeholders in one place. That would include the bike stores and customers for repair and services, buying and selling of used bikes, new bikes, accessories, subscription of bikes (partnered with Ridemovs, Jonna), rent bikes, bike pool and even help the customers with the logistics to pick up and drop off the bike. We are not just connecting the stakeholders but also bringing transparency, openness, fair-pricing and gamification into the biking world.
tags: Marketplace, Internet Publishing, Bicycle Repair Service

name: P27 Nordic Payments
businessDescription: P27 aims to build world's first real-time, cross-border payment system in multiple currencies. P27 will enable real-time, batch, domestic and cross-border payments to be carried out quickly and at low cost on a secure and versatile platform. The platform will initially allow payments to flow instantly between people and businesses within the countries of Denmark, Finland and Sweden, something that will benefit growth and development in the region. The platform will be designed to be expandable to allow for payments across the rest of the Nordics as well, which will contribute to the strengthening of the Nordic paymentâ€™s ecosystem.
tags: Financial Services, FinTech, Mobile Payments, Payments

name: Filestar
businessDescription: With Filestar you can quickly do anything with any file. It is an intuitive software that helps you save time and boost your productivity with tens of thousands of file conversion skills at your fingertips. We live in an insanely fast-developing tech-savvy world. Still, a few years back, in 2018, amazingly little had happened to the way we work with files since the modern desktop came. Millions of people still struggled with frustrating file conversions and transforming large volumes of files. Why wasn’t there a go-to software that safely and effortlessly could solve any daily file-related task? So our founders, who are productivity nerds, set out to build a solution like that. A software that could do anything with any file on any platform. Filestar was born.
tags: Information Technology, Productivity Tools, SaaS, Software

name: Pepicon
businessDescription: Pepicon is a fundraising and exit software based on a proven methodology that helped to raise over 100M EUR of growth capital to Nordic entrepreneurs. Companies to get the pitch right, increasing the odds of raising growth capital with speed and attract investors effortlessly, all while growing their company valuation.  Investors to streamline their deal-flow screening and vetting, eliminating the hassle and time needed to spot winning investment opportunities, while enabling them to take an active role in the companies they invested in. Partners to effectively match the fund-seekers and investors from their network and conduct sound due diligence, while preserving the confidentiality and anonymity of their investors.
tags: Financial Services, FinTech, Funding Platform, Software

name: Pembio
businessDescription: Pembio is founded on a very simple idea: if you know where you’re going, and have at least a rough idea of how to get there, you’re much more likely to end up where you want to be. This is equally true for companies large and small, as well as for teams and individuals. Don’t believe us? Then think of a situation when you didn’t know what to focus on at work, or a time when you didn’t know what to do during a day off; we bet that a little forward planning would have made all the difference! These are some of the values we live by, as a company. We work by them, too: we’re building a platform and products we believe in — knowing there is real value to be gained from helping people, wherever they are, simplify whatever it is that they do and bring more of themselves to their work.
tags: B2B, Collaboration, Information Technology, Internet, Productivity Tools, SaaS, Software

name: Phyron
businessDescription: Phyron is a Swedish SaaS company delivering an AI-video solution for automated large-scale generation of AI videos through a cutting edge technology platform. Phyron solution automatically identifies the unique selling points of each car, new or used. And transforms images, brand videos, text, data, web links and so forth into an attractive video. A video that can be used to promote sales on website/VDP:s and social media as well as in your showroom and other sales presentations. The process is 100% automated, and the capacity unlimited.

name: Picsmart
businessDescription: Picsmart was founded in Stockholm in 2019 with the goal of making food online faster, more efficient and climate-smart. In recent years, the number of opportunities to have your food delivered home has increased, but there is still a lot of room for development. The food industry is the last major market to digitize, which makes our goal of offering climate-smart, fast and personal food deliveries more relevant than ever. We thought that today's way of shopping for food online could be significantly smarter and we therefore decided to build our own service. It all started on a small scale with a single store and we initially delivered pre-ordered breakfast bags with bicycles on Sunday mornings. Since then we have come a long way! Today, Picsmart is active in Stockholm and collaborates with an ever-growing network of local grocery stores. We grow every day and establish ourselves continuously in new areas with new partner stores. From these stores, you as a customer can shop both quickly, cheaply and more climate-smart directly through our platform. Picsmart offers both picking and home delivery of your groceries directly from your local store. As we do not have our own stock but shop directly from your local store, you can shop for exactly the same price as in the store without any unnecessary price surcharges. In addition to the goods, you as a customer only pay the delivery fee, which is the same regardless of how much or how little you choose to buy. We do all this so that you can buy food online at better prices, have the opportunity to get lightning-fast deliveries and to contribute to a better environment. We think this is smart for both you and the planet! Whether you are looking to save time in everyday life, find the best food prices online or have simply missed out on some ingredients for tonight's dinner, we are here for you and ready to make your life a little smoother.
tags: Delivery, Food and Beverage, Food Delivery

name: Pigello
businessDescription: Pigello is a comprehensive property management platform with a focus on a user-friendly interface and automated processes. It is a modular property management system, where all modules are directly integrated to provide an automated flow. Through Pigellos wide range of solutions, businesses can take part in the markets most modern workflow.
tags: Information Services, Information Technology, Property Management

name: Polhem Infra
businessDescription: Polhem Infra is a company that invests in and manages infrastructure assets. The company was founded 2019 and is jointly owned by the AP Funds, First AP Fund, Third AP Fund and Fourth AP Fund. The focus is direct investment in unlisted Swedish or Nordic infrastructure companies in private sector and public sector. The potential areas of investment are infrastructure that is close and crucial to the society such as energy, transport, renewable electricity generation and digital infrastructure.

name: evoli
businessDescription:
evoli is an insurance company that is regulated and licensed by the Swedish Financial Supervisory Authority. evoli was founded in 2019. evoli AB is registered as an insurance intermediary with Finansinspektionen and mediates insurance on the Swedish market. evoli has its liability insurance with Lloyd's Association of Underwriters.

evoli is registered with the Swedish Companies Registration Office and is under the supervision of the Swedish Financial Supervisory Authority and the Swedish Consumer Agency. In Finansinspektionen business register, the advisers who are employed by us are listed. If you want to check the permit and registration for evoli and our employed insurance brokers, this can be done at Finansinspektionen and the Swedish Companies Registration Office, respectively, see contact information below.
tags: Auto Insurance, Financial Services, Insurance, InsurTech

name: Preactlys
businessDescription: Preactly develops HR SAAS tools helping other companies with setting up a digital work environment to support employers and employees. Preactly offers a smart service for mapping underlying factors that create well- being . The service is not a general survey tool but is based on research -based question modules . There are modules for both work and leisure. What can active work environment work mean for the development of your business? To work preventively ? It can be difficult to keep track of how everyone is feeling and what needs to be done to be an attractive workplace .

name: EpinovaTech
businessDescription: EpinovaTech is an electronics company that specializes in manufacturing electronics devices. The company focuses on a new generation of power conversion technology using Gallium Nitride (GaN). It offers fast charging solutions. EpinovaTech was founded in 2019 and headquartered in Skane Lan, Sweden.

name: Emollivet
businessDescription: Emollivet offers a wide range of pet supplies. At Emollivet, we are passionate about developing the traditional animal health industry and giving more influence to you as an animal owner. With user-friendliness in focus, we develop products that work and can easily be used every day. Without impossible requirements. Without a guilty conscience. Without it taking quality time from you and your best friend. We make everyday life easier for pet owners and their pets. Emollivet is an animal health company offering efficient and user-friendly products for animals with skin problems.

name: Profundus Imaging
businessDescription: Profundus Imaging is developed a new fundus camera that could be used to provide researchers and clinicians with a tool that can visualize currently subclinical changes of retinal disease. The camera is built on so-called Adaptive Optics, a technology that is normally used in terrestrial space telescopes and was developed due to a need for improved resolution in retinal imaging and offers 7-10 times higher resolution than conventional instruments over a considerably larger imaging area than competing concepts.

name: Dropmed
businessDescription: Dropmed is a Stockholm-based startup and the independent medical marketplace of the Nordics. For caregivers, Dropmed provides a marketplace allowing them to purchase medical grade products directly from local distributors. Soon, Dropmed will open a second marketplace allowing Nordic caregivers to purchase products directly from vendors anywhere in the EU. For vendors, Dropmed provides a sales platform to target local customer segments with full control over company profile, products, pricing, agreements and content. Soon, Dropmed will open a second platform, allowing vendors from all across the EU find distributors in the Nordics.

name: DSruptive Subdermals
businessDescription: DSruptive is a design agency with expertise in implantable microelectronics and related technologies. DSruptive has developed a proprietary platform for frictionless health logging and remote diagnostics. The platform can, among numerous other applications, be used for early detection of fever both on an individual and on a population level.
tags: Health Care, Personal Health, Wellness, Fitness Services

name: Done
businessDescription: Done provides a mobile platform where consumers get access to quality, vetted craftsmen for their home projects over video chat and have all communication in one place with the mobile app. Founded in Stockholm, Sweden, Done is transforming the way home services are consumed throughout the Nordics. Done is the next generation mobile marketplace for home improvement and repair services. Your on-demand home services marketplace.
tags: Home Improvement, Home Services, Marketplace, Mobile Apps

name: Din Psykolog
businessDescription: Din Psykolog is a fully digital psychologist-service. We use chat first and a smart matching algorithm that matches you with a psychologist that suits your specific needs. These two in combination is a unique way of both lowering the threshold to getting mental help and also makes it significantly easier to find your way and actually start seeing a psychologist. With Din Psykolog you can write to your psychologist whenever and as much as you want - no appointment needed!

name: Dentalum
businessDescription: Dentalum Operations AB is a fast-growing dental service organization focusing on acquiring profitable and sustainable dental clinics in the Nordics. Dentalum's philosophy is built on local heritage, where the clinic owners continue as entrepreneurs operating the clinics with a high degree of independence post-acquisition. Dentalum's goal is to build a world-class organization by creating a strong corporate culture, positive work environment and growth opportunities which motivate and engage our coworkers to provide the highest quality of care and a remarkable service to our patients.

name: SecureBug
businessDescription: Founded in 2019 based in Gothenburg-Sweden by a group of senior cybersecurity specialists with more than two decades of experience in the area, SecureMind Group Ab is the first proactive cybersecurity solution provider in the Scandinavian region aiming to help fill the gaps in cybersecurity in this region. our SecureBug platform is considered the first crowdsourcing security platform developed and implemented by a group of cyber girls by the name of Valkyrie in 2020. SecureBug platform (“SecureBug”) made available by separated unit of the SecureMind Group AB. We create an environment with an open culture where we welcome any expert in our community to share their innovation and expertise regardless of their location. This would hopefully give everyone an equal opportunity. If this sounds good, create your account and join our community.

name: Semicon Service Nordic AB
businessDescription: Semicon Service Nordic is a growing consulting firm focusing on servicing the ASIC / FPGA domain. We connect clients with vetted subject matter experts-talented individuals -from our global professional network.  Our ambition is to expand our services to clients within the Telecom and other industries in the Nordic Region. SSN is a trusted partner for clients considering consulting services. Clients are usually concerned about issues of complexity, timescales and the uncertainty of using an ‘unknown’ consultant from another country.  We recognize these concerns and ensure successful transitions for both client and candidate. At the onset we are about clarity of focus, uniform process and strong project management. Secondly, we work with a trusted partner who can share their knowledge of an existing clientsorganization, its operating style, culture and people requirements. We believe with everyone involved in the process, there is more maturity, accuracy and flexibility in the process.

name: Skinfo
businessDescription: By combining scientific data from multiple sources and presenting it in an easy-to-understand format, we are building the first-ever scalable solution for Europe’s 500 million personal care consumers. The market penetration of some cosmetic products, like deodorants and shampoos, is near 100%. Our goal is to make the industry completely transparent, so that you as a customer know what your products contain and what they actually do for your skin and health. To change a whole industry, you need both time and patience, combined with hard work. This is something that we at Skinfo work with on a daily basis, pushing the industry forward, step by step. While many people wear no makeup or use no hair styling products, nearly everyone has some form of skincare product, even if it’s just a bottle of lotion or a tube of sunscreen.
tags: B2B, Beauty, Cosmetics, E-Commerce, Information Technology, Personal Health, SaaS

name: SNAFU Records
businessDescription: The Snafu team is a unique blend of world-class songwriters, top technical talent, and music industry veterans. Our team has worked with some of the biggest artists in the world, including Ariana Grande, Frank Ocean, Avicii, Nicki Minaj, The Weeknd, Taylor Swift, Armaan Malik, and Foster The People, to name a few. Our Grammy-nominated songwriting team have penned dozens of Billboard-topping songs, and collaborate with our roster to make many more.  Snafu is a hybrid tech and music company, with the heart of a record label and the mind of a startup. Our proprietary algorithms analyze millions of data points from over 150,000 songs per week, identifying artists whose music is undervalued and needs amplifying.

name: Coupleness
businessDescription: Coupleness, founded in 2019 by Ted Rosen and CEO Jenny Holmstrom, developed a mobile app aimed to act as a common micro-diary for couples who want to communicate more with each other. We at Coupleness are all about making it easy for couples to take care of their relationships. Together with our users, we have created the tool that we needed in our lives. Using Coupleness is a way to be proactive and build positive habits in everyday life. Join the movement and become a couple that embraces what it means to invest in your relationship.

name: Confirma Software
businessDescription: Confirma Software is a vertical software platform that acquires strong enterprise software companies. Confirma Software is a leading Nordic software company offering solutions to small- and medium sized companies and the public sector. Confirma Software is committed to continue the successful operation of each of its subsidiaries under their existing brands and with existing management. Each company will contribute their unique experience and expertise in developing a strong joint operating platform across the Nordics.

name: Commended.ai
businessDescription:
Commended.ai is a platform connecting independent consultants with work. By collecting digital references (grading consultants skills) and combining this unique data with AI, we enable consultants to prove their worth - and those looking for consultants to screen candidates on actual skills instead of guessing who to talk to from a pile of CVs. 

Commended is a platform that utilizes machine learning to create a smoother running market for independent consultants. A market that employs millions of professionals but that is held back by poor transparency around who is good at what, wants to do what, is available when and at what price?

Our platform has been used to identify qualified consultants for more than 30 companies. It helps consultants to prove their value far beyond a CV. Consultants not only grade their skills but can obtain skill gradings from clients and colleagues.
tags: Artificial Intelligence, Human Resources, Information Technology, Machine Learning

name: Stockrepublic
businessDescription: We provide a trustworthy and engaging way of empowering bank and broker customers in the world of mutual funds and stocks. We offer a partnership to use our social trading platform with ready applications (mobile, web, desktop) and API's for providing the end-users with insights, benchmarking and collaboration with the most trustworthy source there is, real people taking good care of their own money.

name: Stratipath Medical
businessDescription:
We are on a mission to radically improve treatment decisions and outcomes in cancer care through fast, precise and affordable solutions for diagnosis, prognosis and stratification of cancer patients. Our vision
is that every person with cancer gets the right treatment at the right time. This would improve the lives of millions of people around the world, while substantially reducing the global costs of healthcare.We leverage artificial intelligence combined with very large population representative data sets and associated clinical outcome data, to provide decision support tools and second read solutions to pathology labs and oncology clinics, as well helping pharma and biotech companies identify patients who benefit from novel therapies.

name: Celcibus
businessDescription: Celcibus AB is a Swedish innovation company with strong expertise in materials for clean energy solutions. Its patented catalyst was developed to provide fuel cells with sustainable, high-performance, noble-metal free power solutions for transport, household, and industrial applications. The hydrogen economy requires more sustainable and cheaper fuel cells. Celcibus catalyses the future. Celcibus develops solutions for sustainable energy systems. The initial products are fuel cell components based on a unique, patented catalyst which is free from platinum group metals, and can thus be produced less expensively and with less environmental impact.

name: Surfboard Payments
businessDescription: Surfboard Payments is a Swedish-based software developer employing around 45 people in Stockholm, Sweden and Chennai, India. Surfboard Payments is developing payment software and creating new checkout touchpoints which consumers face when completing their purchases. All development is done with the customer journey in primary focus, ensuring an easy checkout experience identical across devices. The dynamic and interactive screens enable marketing to the right person at the right time, in the right place.

name: Symbiome.io
businessDescription: With the help of our app, you can easily absorb all the information from your test results. There is also a user forum where you can exchange tips and ideas with others. Also install the app to do health tests and get an indication of whether your stomach may be behind your health problems.

name: Swedish Temptations
businessDescription: We thought that there was a lack of a plant-based alternative on the market that was actually kind to both the environment, climate and health - at the same time. Something really good on Swedish and organic raw materials with low climate impact, made in Sweden. Vegan, gluten-free and without additives. Preferably whole grains ... and with a manufacturing process that reduces food waste in production. So, we decided to do it ourselves and include everything where we think is important (all of the above). The result is Bärta®, a sprouted and fermented yellow pea. Yellow peas are the most climate-smart we can eat and therefore the choice fell on them. Peas are cool no matter what, so be it. Today we are the Swedish vegan food manufacturer for everyone who is hungry for good, healthy and sustainable food. We are driven by passion for food, playfulness and a desire to do good things. Well, it's a little tricky for us to make a product that is really useful on the planet, but it's easy for you and everyone else who wants to eat within the planet's boundaries. And that's the whole thing.  Bärta® is manufactured by Swedish Temptations AB. The peas are grown in Sweden and fermented into culinary delights in our production kitchen in Karlshamn. We hope you had the opportunity to taste.

name: SWATI Cosmetics
businessDescription: The story of SWATI starts with two people falling in love. Vishal Nanda meets Swati Verma. Boom. Like all great love stories, it transcends borders. Vishal is an experienced Swedish entrepreneur, Swati a well-known Indian makeup artist. He’s struck by her appearance and how it changes with every mood and occasion. A natural beauty one day. Dressed to impress the next. Yet she always looks like herself. Confident. Stylish. Remarkably enough, even her eyes seem to change. From bright to dark and back again. He asks. “Cosmetic lenses,” she replies smiling. The rest is, as they say, history.

name: Tecta
businessDescription: Tecta builds next-generation digital tools for the real estate industry. Tecta was founded in Karlskrona in 2019. We offer property owners and managers a digital tool for property management. A completely cloud-based platform for taking control of your financial and technical management. We offer property owners and managers a digital tool for property management. A completely web-based platform for taking control of your financial and technical management. We collect and digitize information regarding agreements, invoicing, case management and credit assessment, all information about your properties in one place. A platform that simplifies and streamlines the administrative work for real estate companies and their tenants.

name: Tengai
businessDescription: Tengai AB an interview intelligence platform utilizing artificial intelligence and behavioral science in an interview product suite for recruitment. The software is easily integrated in any applicant tracking system and contributes to automation, speed and science-backed hiring for recruiters and hiring managers. The interview product suite consists of Tengai Recruit, Tengai Automated Video Interview, and Tengai Robot. The interview suite enhances candidate experience and leverage validated behavior science and interview data for screening applicants at the beginning of the recruitment funnel. The interview intelligence data helps recruiters and hiring managers to make more informed and better hiring decisions and to reduce time to hire, which makes it a great tool for high-volume recruiting.
tags: Artificial Intelligence, Human Computer Interaction, Human Resources, Machine Learning, Recruiting, Robotics, SaaS, Social Recruiting, Software

name: Texelio
businessDescription: Texelio offers a range of API solutions to retail investor trading platforms that radically improves the end user stock market news experience. Blending natural language programming and analytics, our customers increase user retention, insight and commission income. It is a deep-tech SaaS platform that radically increases the usability and delivery of financial media while driving insights, engagement and revenues. Offering 100+ contextual topics available for equities, ESG, commodities and cryptos.
tags: Artificial Intelligence, Financial Services, Language Learning, Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing

name: TensionCam
businessDescription: TensionCam Systems AB is a vital startup company based in Gothenburg of Sweden. Commercialising the patented TensionCam concept we offer a one stop shop in monitoring clamp load in industrial bolt joints. The company was formed early 2019 after successful development proceedings as a project within G-coder Systems AB (www.g-coder.com). This company was founded in 2005 by Olle Takman and Jonas Nilsagård and offers advanced 4D joysticks. The sensor technology used in the joysticks is in principal the same as for the TensionCam concept.

name: Carcare Systems Europe
businessDescription: Carcare is an automated process tool that monitors your inventory of used cars. Carcare retrieves data from your DMS and automation means that you do not need to get into how the system works technically. With Carcare, all cars lead times are measured, from exchange to delivery and every step in between. In order to streamline and gain control throughout the process, the right person in the flow of used cars receives notifications by email about what to do with the car or if a car is stuck in the process. The statistics in Carcare allow you to compare different time periods, departments and external suppliers to see if you are making progress. It also works great to see how your external suppliers deliver the right services, quickly and efficiently.

name: Cangoroo Tech
businessDescription: Cangoroo, an innovative MaaS company, are bringing shared app-based pogo sticks and other urban commuting solutions to every street corner of the world. Literally jump on a Cangoroo anytime and cruise your way through the city. Fun. Healthy. Convenient. 100% Emission free. Founded by Adam Mikkelsen, Eric Calderon and David Axelsson in Jan 2019, with its headquarters in Malmö, southern Sweden.
tags: Apps, CleanTech, Electric Vehicle, Information Technology

name: Tilly
businessDescription: Tilly was founded with the mission of helping people reduce (in)fertility stress and time to pregnancy. Initially focusing on science-based motivational and educational support - personalised throughout the entire fertility journey using a data-driven approach.

name: Usurpator AB
businessDescription: Wolfpack is a multiplayer co-op U-boat simulation game where a team of players man the stations of a German type VII U-boat during the second world war. Several crews may play together in a wolfpack, completing missions based on iconic events during the different stages of german U-boat war between 1939 and 1945. Wolfpack is not only a community based project, but also also a Co-Op game where the core feature is playing with other people. This pushes the need for an active community even further, and we strive to encourage people to form new U-boat crews, be part of the discussion and sharing their thoughts and opinions both with us and with fellow players. We very much encourage streaming of the game, so do not hesitate to contact us if you are a streamer/let's player.

name: Volta Trucks
businessDescription: We are building a full electric truck specifically to be used in and around cities and urban areas. No tailpipe emissions, no engine noise. And without a bulky diesel engine we’re also able to completely re-design the cabin with a driver-centric approach to make the vehicle safer for drivers, pedestrians and cyclists. The driver seat has literally been placed in the center and the cab lowered to optimise the driver’s field of view and to allow easy access on both sides with sliding doors. In short, we’re ripping up the design book on urban trucks and starting again.
tags: Automotive, Electric Vehicle, Last Mile Transportation, Logistics

name: ARC
businessDescription: ARC is a consulting group that transforms businesses and brands to help drive digital growth. ARC combines the best talents in the industry of change. From pioneering management consultants and brand creatives to digital experts – Above, Animal, Ariel, Conversionista, Cupole, Curamando, Kurppa Hosk, Nameless.today and Umain have come together to form ARC. We are here to help people, businesses and brands arise through digital transformation. We create digital growth that transforms businesses and brands. A group of consciously selected experts. Brought together to make our clients winners in a transformative landscape. Our vision is to become the benchmark of our industry by making our clients the benchmark of theirs.
tags: Advertising, Management Consulting, Marketing, Social Media

name: WeTal
businessDescription: WeTal is a career marketplace that connects developers with Stockholm's most innovative companies. It’s created for developers by developers. We believe recruiting should be a transparent, unbiased, and enjoyable experience for both the company and the candidate. WeTal’s mission is to make hiring, or getting hired faster, easier, and more enjoyable.

name: Wiser Media
businessDescription: We are WireWallet; a smart, and safe way to send and receive funds! WireWallet was founded in 2019, offering payment solutions to businesses and individuals. Our online banking platform allows businesses a to create one or more accounts and receive their very own dedicated IBAN. Hence, our users are able to invoice their customers, as well as collect payments, which are sent to an IBAN in their own company name. Our users enjoy a fully interactive back-office platform, where they can manage their funds, perform currency exchanges, and pay out in over 100 global currencies. We also provide dedicated account managers for each of our merchant’s accounts, and therefore they always have a single point of call should they need any questions answered.
tags: Banking, Finance, Financial Services, FinTech, Payments

name: Angelchat
businessDescription:
Instant messaging app that anonymously matches and pairs users who seek or provide support on emotional challenges. We help combat the mental health epidemic by matching and connecting people to offer or seek help anonymously in an app. The founders of Angelchat are Johan and Karolina, two senior entrepreneurs in digital from Stockholm, Sweden.

Sweden is one of the most developed welfare states in the world, where everyone is taken care of and families are granted 480 days paid parental leave per child. Despite this impressive system many people still keep suffering from mental health issues.
tags: Health Care, Lifestyle, Mobile Apps, Personal Health

name: Wiser Media
businessDescription: Wiser is a social curation platform and discovery tool for podcasts, videos, articles and audiobooks. We bring a holistic, human-centred approach to content discovery as opposed to algorithmic solutions that create echo chambers. On Wiser, in real time, you can discover curations created by friends, family, colleagues as well as intellectual influencers — who we call "Wisers". It all begins with an idea. Maybe you want to launch a business. Maybe you want to turn a hobby into something more. Or maybe you have a creative project to share with the world. Whatever it is, the way you tell your story online can make all the difference.

name: All Aboard
businessDescription: Explore more in Europe: Train travel gives you the chance to explore more places than one. Make the journey part of the destination. Plan & book in one place: Get recommended routes based on expert trips. Adjust them to your needs and book all tickets at once. Simple & safe. Sustainable travel choice: Look after the planet and travel by train. You reduce your carbon footprint and help to cut global emissions. Win-win. We make it easy to explore routes, plan trips and book train tickets to the next sustainable European adventure. All in one place - It’s as simple as that!

name: AirForestry
businessDescription: AirForestry develops technology solutions that enables electric drones usage on forest thinning. It provides sustainable ways and equipment to clear out forests. AirForestry was founded in 2019 and is based in Uppsala, Sweden. AirForestry's groundbreaking technology makes it possible to thin out the forests in a completely new way, namely from the air with high-capacity drones. Through our innovative thinning, we contribute to reducing carbon dioxide emissions from forestry work while increasing the forest's ability to sequester carbon. We’re #ReinventingForestry with electric drones.

name: Accurator
businessDescription: Accurator is a software developer from Sweden providing a smart purchasing solution for people working in the construction industry. Accurator is a Swedish innovation with the goal of streamlining the purchasing process in the construction sector. Our cloud-based tool saves 50-70% of the administrative time for buyers who can instead spend that time on negotiation and profitability. The purchasing tool for the construction industry.

name: Acorai

name: MedTech Concept
businessDescription:
Medtech Concept AB was founded in 2019 with a vision to become the leading supplier of miniature injection devices globally. 
The company will launch its first product Minipen 2 which will be the smallest injection device in the world. 
The Minipen 2 is three times smaller than existing injection pens, with a narrow-gauge short needle to reduce pain, suitable for vaccinations, cosmetic procedures and 300+ million insulin injecting diabetics.  
We aim to capture 1% of the global market for diabetic injection devices estimated to be worth over $0.5 billion USD per annum.  
Due to an unprecedented demand for injection devices, we have accelerated our product launch plans and now have 15 distributors lined up to purchase the Minipen by the container load. 
We have two factories ready to start manufacturing to meet the anticipated global demand, fuelled by a rapid global increase in diabetes and global vaccination programmes. To set the factory up, we need to arrange funding in the form of loans, convertible loans or sale of equity.
longBusinessDescription:
Problem
Diabetics injecting insulin currently use large cumbersome medical devices in the form of insulin pens and medical syringes (not designed for self injection) up to six times a day. The syringes are far from portable and attract attention when used in public places. The pens are portable but bulky, difficult to carry on the person, are easily broken and need to be refrigerated to preserve the insulin which degrades with heat.
Solution
We will bring our miniature injection device Minipen to the following markets:
- People with diabetes injecting insulin (Type 1 & 2)
- Cosmetic markets
- Medical vaccination & Immunisation programmes
- Veterinary Use
Manufacturing of the Minipen is due to begin in August 2021 subject to financing having been secured in January 2021.
We have a pipeline of 15 clients, two distributor’s have already signed contracts and we expect to sign by the end of January 2021.
We are seeking Trade Finance to fund 12 months of OPEX and the CAPEX required to set-up a production line with US Company Darco Corporation.
Details of the finance required can be found in a separate document  referenced as Debt Market Proposal.
Small investors can obtain shares in the Swedish company please ask for details.
A private placement offer has been created for corporates to support the company via a convertible loan, giving the option to have the loan repaid after two years or converted into equity/stock at a pre-agreed price.

name: Safety-Bolts
businessDescription:
SAFETY bolt is a predictive maintenance IIoT sensor technology for measurement of bolt strain.

SAFETY BOLT is the only heavy industry bolt-strain sensor technology that solves the painful tradeoffs in existing strain measurement, which are: Retrofitting, cost, scale, consistency, accuracy, human safety, manual control, reliability, ease of installation and maintainability.     

SAFETY BOLT stands unique in predictive bolt strain sensor innovation, and quantifiably can save 50% more lives in heavy industry sites annually, reduce operational maintenance costs by up to 20%, and avoid unplanned downtime costing up to 1$mil a day.
longBusinessDescription:
Reinforcing bolts are a fundamental safety component in structures. If a bolt breaks, not only can lives be lost, but costly operational downtime, and incalculable societal impact results. Sensor measurement of bolt strain is a business critical function.
Pressure on mines and wind farms to balance resource exploitation and sustainability, while maximising competitiveness, cost efficiencies, and safety - is challenging. They have struggled for many years to find a bolt strain tech that can scale without compromising safety and cost. 
SAFETY BOLT is the only solution today that offers to solve the painful tradeoffs demanded by existing strain measurement sensor tech, which are: Retrofitting, cost, scale, consistency, accuracy, human safety, manual control, reliability, ease of installation and maintainability.     
SAFETY BOLT stands unique in predictive bolt strain sensor measurement innovation, and quantifiably can save heavy industry up to 50% more lives annually, reduce operational maintenance costs by up to 20%, and avoid unplanned downtime costing up to 1$mil a day.

longBusinessDescription:

*Risk reduction in customer losses for the companies
*Proposition of a new adjusted returns for institutional investors looking for a new asset class
INVOIER offers first-of-its-kind real time Invoice Spot Market with better risk classification. At the heart of our solution is an AI element which makes possible a much more focused and accurate risk assessment as our tool is able to predict the actual pay-day of the traded invoice. Thus, with the AI element in place we are able to introduce a unique and completely new way of measuring risk for individual receivables as opposed to risk with individual companies. By harnessing our AI solution to the INVOIER Invoice Spot Market, we deliver a wholly new level of market transparency and engagement on the part of: the sellers - who will now be able to participate more actively knowing the market value of their invoices (real time prices) and buyers – getting access to completely new asset classification.

name: MIPARO
businessDescription: Online property listing portal for emerging markets. Very much like America's Zillow or the U.K.'s RightMove except it only operates in developing countries, not Europe (with one exception) and the U.S.
longBusinessDescription:
MIPARO lists homes for sale in a variety of emerging markets. They not only showcase homes for sale globally, they also provide their broker clients with buyer leads. The property portal category is very mature in the developed countries of Europe, the U.S., Australia, South Africa, and Japan. However, in emerging markets, where Internet penetration and usage lags, listing portals are just coming into their own. Typically, dozens of broker sites and listing platforms exist in these countries. Few feature an area's entire inventory. It very difficult for domestic and international buyers to navigate these platforms, and often, language and the trust factor - there are a lot of scam artists - remain a problem too.
MIPARO's goal is to be the "go-to" platform for buyers and sellers in the real estate market in emerging markets. They hope to consolidate housing inventory so buyers don't have to visit countless websites. Furthermore, MIPARO seeks to assist brokers and agent by providing leads and offering CRM-type products so agents can devote more of their time to developing customer relationships, and less on managing data and book keeping.
To date, MIPARO is the leading online listing platform in Bangladesh and the second largest in the Philippines. They are launching a crowdfunding campaign on May 21 with FundedByMe to acquire capital to expand into India, Thailand and other emerging markets.
tags: property listings, real estate, emerging markets

businessDescription:
The Stockholm-based startup, which was founded in 2018, has now raised €3.1 million and is already trusted by customers across different industries, including FMCG, consumer goods, heavy industry, defence, automotive, and charity – showing real promise for the future of the company. 

Unlike its competitors that just calculate and visualize Share of Search from Google data, My Telescope bolsters the use of search data with its proprietary AI solution that scans, visualizes, and more importantly, analyzes sentiment data. Data taken from the media, social listening, forums, and product reviews can be used to gain deeper insights into the underlying intentions behind the search activity. Through this deep data analysis, My Telescope is able to provide more actionable recommendations for future marketing investments.

he problem is that a lot of money is invested into building a brand, but previously there hasn’t been any way of proving in real-time that the investment is actually driving you anywhere. It basically means that the whole industry pumps money into a black hole and waits months to find out the results. However, the correlation between what people search and sales numbers and market share has been scientifically proven.  My Telescope helps the marketing industry to prove the impact much faster through almost real-time analytics, reporting and dashboards on the Share of Search data – and that marketing investments generate business-critical impacts.

longBusinessDescription:
Unbiased AB is a tech company based in Sweden, Fighting Fake News and Misinformation with a focus on futuristic innovation and next-generation technology. The areas we are focused on currently include Blockchain technology, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, and Natural Language Processing.
It's no secret that the current social media and Internet platforms have many flaws when it comes to transparency, privacy, and false information. With increasingly biased news in traditional media combined with false information on the Internet, people across the globe are not able to make decisions based on reliable data and insights. Fake News is not only affecting us as individuals but also our communities at large.
We are addressing the problem of Bias in technology, Fake news and the fact that it is difficult to follow up on the origin of news, data and information. We are approaching this complex problem in a staged manner whereby we start at the core algorithm level of applications and we scale to the end-user interaction level. We believe that one single solution cannot address this issue, the only way to address this problem is by educating people, enterprises, communities and empowering them with necessary tools & solutions.
tags: Blockchain, AI, ML, BigData, Fight against Fake News, Data Marketplace, Search Engine, Social Platform

longBusinessDescription:
Scaleout was launched in 2017 as a spinoff from the Distributed Computing Applications (DCA) Research Group at the Department of Information Technology at Uppsala University. Founded by Andreas Hellander, associate professor in computational science, assistant professor Salman Toor and associate professor Ola Spjuth, the original aim was to enable advanced scientific cloud computing and AI solutions in industrial applications and early customer cases focused on cloud-native applications and big data consultancy.
Daniel Zakrisson, Morgan Ekmefjord and Jens Frid, entrepreneurs with a background in blockchain technology, joined as co-founders in 2018 to focus on business and product development, and the convergence of AI and decentralized technologies.
As a research and innovation partner, we help you turn your visions into the intelligent applications of tomorrow. We are experienced cloud architects, DevOps engineers, and data scientists and with deep expertise in ML/AI, Cloud-native computing, Data science & engineering, and Scientific computing & HPC. We can help ensure that your project runs smoothly and that the developed solutions are designed in a sustainable way. Our experts can help you understand the requirements, the optimal use of available resources and build scalable, end-to-end cost-effective solutions.
Our specialist team of consultants, researchers, scientists, engineers, and developers can provide a complete solution to deliver end-to-end AI success. We have delivered valuable research and consultation services in the pharmaceutical industry, a leading paper and packaging manufacturer, a world leader in software for radiation therapy, a provider of manufacturing software solutions, one of the largest ferry and shipping operators in the world, the Swedish national space agency, and others.
